{
  "text": "Patients received six cycles (28 days per cycle) of ifosfamide at 5.0 g/m 2 and carboplatin at 300 mg/m 2 intravenously on day 1, etoposide at 180 mg/m 2 intravenously on days 1 and 2, and uromitexan at 5.0 g/m 2 on days 1 and 2 [CITATION_1] . No dose reduction was permitted. Chemotherapy was delayed up to 2 weeks in the presence of nonhematologic toxicity grade 3 or greater (except nausea, diarrhea, or alopecia) and if creatinine clearance was less than 50 mL/min, leukocyte concentrations were less than 3 \u00d7 10 9 /L, and platelet concentrations were less than 30 \u00d7 10 9 /L.",
